oakcurric:unit-2913
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "New experiences: perfect tense with 'haben' and 'sein'"@en ;
  curric:slug "new-experiences-perfect-tense-with-haben-and-sein" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits the perfect tense with both haben and sein, as well as a range
  of sound-symbol correspondences.Within the context of new experiences, pupils can apply
  this to school, home or travel experiences."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Building on prior knowledge of the perfect tense or weak and strong verbs
  with haben and sein, and the use of prepositions 'in' and 'auf' with accusative and dative,
  pupils apply their knowledge and growing high frequency vocabulary knowledge in a school
  context. Cultural context is also provided as the knowledge is applied in a tourist/cultural
  visit to Salzburg, Austria.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2913-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2913-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2913-3 ;
  curric:id "2913"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.299271Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-be-being ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-have-having .

oakcurric:unit-2909
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Past journeys: perfect tense with 'sein'"@en ;
  curric:slug "past-journeys-perfect-tense-with-sein" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces the German perfect tense with 'sein' for verbs of movement,
  practising it in contrast to the perfect tense with 'haben' in singular forms. 'Mit' is
  introduced with modes of transport allowing pupils to practise word order manner before
  place."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils continue to develop their understanding of the perfect tense in
  German, as this unit introduces the contrast between verbs using haben and those verbs mostly
  of movement to a destination which use 'sein' plus past participle. Modes of transport are
  introduced with the preposition 'mit' (dative). Pupils extend their knowledge of word order
  with manner before place. Previous knowledge of prepositions is reactivated and practised
  with 'mit' and 'durch'. The unit context is a traditional German school trip to the popular
  Black Forest.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2909-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2909-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2909-3 ;
  curric:id "2909"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.405734Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-be-being ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions .

oakcurric:unit-2912
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Family and friends: verbs with indirect objects"@en ;
  curric:slug "family-and-friends-verbs-with-indirect-objects" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces verbs with indirect objects in familiar contexts involving
  family and friends. Pupils apply this in terms of exchanging gifts, and giving a range of
  opinions using verbs such as 'gefallen'. Word order 2 and 3 are revisited as pupils give
  opinions with or without 'dass'."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Developing the thread of giving opinions, pupils learn the concept of
  verbs with indirect objects within the context of exchanging gifts. Accusative and dative are
  revisited with the prepositions 'für' and 'von'. Pupils build knowledge and confidence in
  giving opinions and reasons with a broader range of opinion verbs, and revisiting word order
  3 with verbs with 'weil' and 'dass'. Pupils apply this knowledge in a range of familiar
  contexts.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2912-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2912-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2912-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2912-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2912-5 ;
  curric:id "2912"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.508495Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order .

oakcurric:unit-2926
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Desires, plans and priorities: 'möcht-' future and use of infinitive"@en ;
  curric:slug "desires-plans-and-priorities-mocht-future-and-use-of-infinitive" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit extends knowledge of the future tense for all persons, and introduces
  'möcht-' , with nouns and in two-verb structures. Using the infinite with 'es ist' +
  adjective, zu + infinitive extends pupils' ability to give views and opinions.
  Prepositions with accusative and dative are revisited."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit extends pupils' ability to express desires and plans with
  'möcht-', used with a noun and with an infinitive in a two-verb structure. Pupils extend
  their knowledge and use of the future tense, contrasting it with verbs like 'vorhaben' as
  they revisit zu +infinitive. Vocabulary is extended as pupils express both immediate desires
  at a Christmas market and longer term plans, challenges and priorities. Pupils ask and answer
  questions on what they did with and for others, reactivating knowledge of prepositions.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2926-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2926-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2926-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2926-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2926-5 ;
  curric:id "2926"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.545348Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives .

oakcurric:unit-2907
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Who am I? Adjective agreement, 'weil' and 'denn'"@en ;
  curric:slug "who-am-i-adjective-agreement-weil-and-denn" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces prenominal adjective agreement in nominative and accusative
  cases. It equips pupils with the knowledge to describe themselves and others in more
  detail. It will also analyse how to vary giving reasons with 'denn' (word order 1) or
  'weil' (word order 3)."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Building on pupils' prior knowledge and frequent revisiting of nouns and
  articles in the nominative and accusative cases, this unit introduces (prenominal) adjective
  agreement. Pupils learn to apply this knowledge in descriptions of themselves and others.
  Drawing on previously taught grammar on word order 1 and verbs of opinion (mögen, finden),
  pupils extend their descriptions of themselves by adding reasons with the conjunction 'denn',
  and 'weil' with word order 3. Pupils explore and adapt an authentic text to express personal
  likes and dislikes more creatively.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2907-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2907-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2907-3 ;
  curric:id "2907"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.547580Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts .

oakcurric:unit-2897
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Famous lives: present tense (singular) weak verbs"@en ;
  curric:slug "famous-lives-present-tense-singular-weak-verbs" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores the manipulation of singular persons of weak verbs in question
  and answer forms. It also provides pupils with an important cultural insight into the
  lives of famous historical and present German-speaking personalities. Pupils practise the
  sound-symbol correspondence [er]."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils continue to consolidate their knowledge of present tense weak verbs
  in this unit whilst learning more about a range of famous German speakers, past and present.
  Pupils apply their knowledge in a more challenging context with extended reading, listening
  and writing tasks. Foundations are laid for writing and speaking tasks (interviews and
  conversations) in later units as pupils practise manipulating verbs between (singular)
  subjects in question and answer form.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2897-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2897-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2897-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2897-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2897-5 ;
  curric:id "2897"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.726256Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions .

oakcurric:unit-2931
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Ambitions and destinations: 'mögen', 'möcht-', past tenses"@en ;
  curric:slug "ambitions-and-destinations-mogen-mocht-past-tenses" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits a broad range of known grammar and vocabulary and present and
  past tenses, as pupils learn how to use their knowledge in new contexts of personal goals,
  travel destinations and volunteering."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit revisits known grammar, vocabulary and sound-symbol
  correspondences, so that pupils can talk about what they like, would like and prefer in a
  range of contexts. Large numbers are revisited in the context of statistics on the German
  school system. Dates are revisited in the context of the German artist Franz Marc.
  Preferences, using gern, lieber and other comparative adverbs, are examined with reference to
  travel destinations. and the past tense is revisited in volunteering roles. Pupils apply
  their knowledge in speaking and writing interactions, including describing photos.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2931-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2931-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2931-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2931-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2931-5 ;
  curric:id "2931"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.786699Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional .

oakcurric:unit-2924
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Everyday culture: present tense weak and strong verbs"@en ;
  curric:slug "everyday-culture-present-tense-weak-and-strong-verbs" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits strong and weak verbs in all persons, as well as numbers,
  question formation, negation and adjective agreement. Vocabulary is revisited and extended
  as pupils describe event preparations, pictures and paintings."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Consolidation of the present tense continues in this unit as pupils build
  on recent prior knowledge of 'ihr' (you informal) in contrast to er/sie/es. Existing
  vocabulary knowledge is extended as pupils describe birthday celebrations. Cultural
  background is provided with the iconic '99 Lufballons' song. Pupils deepen their
  understanding of negation, possessive adjectives and adjective agreement as they apply these
  in describing pictures (orally) and a painting (in writing). Places and paintings in
  German-speaking countries and cultural context.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2924-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2924-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2924-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2924-4 ;
  curric:id "2924"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.788830Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-negation .

oakcurric:unit-2910
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Likes and dislikes: adverb 'gern'"@en ;
  curric:slug "likes-and-dislike-adverb-gern" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces the adverb of manner 'gern', practising it in questions with
  'welch-' and in giving opinion answers. The unit revisits word order 1 and 2 and negation
  with nicht."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Refreshing pupils' knowledge of the present tense and giving opinions,
  this unit extends pupils' ability to express likes and dislikes using 'gern', an adverb of
  manner. Knowledge of word order and negation is reactivated and practised in question and
  answer form. Cultural context is provided with an introduction to Vienna.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2910-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2910-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2910-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2910-4 ;
  curric:id "2910"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.791463Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-negation ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions .

oakcurric:unit-2908
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Berlin: numbers and time"@en ;
  curric:slug "berlin-numbers-and-time" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit develops pupils' knowledge of strong verbs in the present tense with the
  introduction of stem changes e-i and a-ä. It will introduce larger numbers (32-100).
  Pupils will practise telling the time using the perfect tense in the 'ich' and 'wir' form."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit deepens pupils' prior knowledge of strong verbs in the present
  tense, and the perfect tense with haben with new vocabulary and a richer verb lexicon. Object
  pronouns are revisited and knowledge deepened with the addition of 'mich' and 'dich'. Pupils
  expand their use of the perfect tense adding the first person plural. Pupils build their
  knowledge of number formation (32-100) in a rich context of authentic German articles on the
  environment. Telling the time is introduced and pupils practise this in the core thread of
  asking and answering questions.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2908-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2908-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2908-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2908-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2908-5 ;
  curric:id "2908"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.811924Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts .

oakcurric:unit-2906
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "An exchange: present tense, 'haben' and 'sein', formal 'Sie' vs 'du', cases"@en ;
  curric:slug "an-exchange-perfect-tense-formal-sie-vs-du" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores the use of the formal 'Sie' (you) vs the informal 'du'. It
  equips pupils with the knowledge to structure richer sentences, using infinitive clauses
  with 'zu', and how to apply their previous knowledge of question forms, gender and cases
  to add new words to their vocabulary."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit draws on pupils' prior knowledge of 'haben' and 'sein' and
  subject pronouns (singular and plural wir and sie (they). Pupils build on this as they learn
  the formal 'Sie' (you) vs the informal 'du' within the context of an exchange visit to a
  German speaking family.. Pupils also learn additional colloquial expressions with haben used
  frequently in the context of home life. Previous learning of core question forms, and the
  alphabet is reactivated, as pupils apply this in a realistic context to find out the meaning
  of unknown words.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2906-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2906-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2906-3 ,
