oakcurric:unit-2902
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Friendship: weak and irregular verbs, simple v. continuous"@en ;
  curric:slug "friendship-weak-and-strong-verbs-simple-v-continuous" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit deepens pupils' knowledge of their verb lexicon. It consolidates their
  understanding of the English present simple and present continuous to translate the German
  present tense, with practice in both question and statement forms. Pupils practise the
  sound-symbol correspondence [j]"""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit continues to develop pupils' understanding and accurate use of
  weak and strong verbs and the reuse of known vocabulary, this time in the context of
  friendship. It consolidates the essential knowledge of the verbs 'sein' and 'haben' and the
  key linguistic differences between the German present tense and the English present simple
  and present continuous. It requires pupils to consolidate their previously taught knowledge
  of word order and question formation as they apply it to conversations about building new
  friendships.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2902-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2902-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2902-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2902-4 ;
  curric:id "2902"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.864983Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions .

oakcurric:unit-2937
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Storytelling: imperfect tense"@en ;
  curric:slug "narrating-a-story-imperfect-tense" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces the imperfect (simple past) tense of regular and highly
  frequent irregular verbs in singular persons.Da- compounds are revisited along with the
  perfect tense and the historic present in the narration of a story."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit, designed around an adaptation of Grimm Brothers' fairy tale of
  the Pied Piper of Hamelin (Der Rattenfänger) uses a famous literary base to introduce the
  imperfect tense for narration. Pupils also practise their knowledge of the new tense in
  contrast with the present tense..""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2937-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2937-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2937-3 ;
  curric:id "2937"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.866887Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts .

oakcurric:unit-2918
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Making plans: present and future tenses"@en ;
  curric:slug "making-plans-present-and-future-tenses" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits and consolidates the present tense, including modal verbs and
  two-verb structures before introducing the future tense in singular persons. It also
  addresses the distinction between the German 'ich will' vs the English 'I want to'."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit initially revisits pupils' knowledge of the present tense to
  communicate future meaning with the use of time phrases and enables pupils to describe and
  write their plans for the week. Pupils then refresh their knowledge of modal verbs and
  two-verb structures, revisiting known verbs and introducing 'sollen', as they examine who
  should do what. Later in the unit, the future tense is introduced in singular persons, as
  pupils use the new tense for future weekend plans. Cultural context is consolidated with
  further references to the Bodensee.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2918-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2918-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2918-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2918-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2918-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2918-6 ;
  curric:id "2918"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.985952Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions .

oakcurric:unit-2892
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Belongings: 'haben' and articles in accusative case"@en ;
  curric:slug "belongings-haben-and-articles-in-accusative-case" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces pupils to the verb 'haben', and the use of the accusative
  case with definite and indefinite articles. Simple classroom conversations are developed
  using yes/no questions and negation with 'kein'. Pupils practise new sound-symbol
  correspondences [w] and [ie].."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces the verb 'haben' (to have). This requires pupils to
  recall and consolidate their previous knowledge of gender and articles and apply it when
  using the accusative case with haben in statements and simple yes/no questions.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2892-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2892-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2892-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2892-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2892-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2892-6 ;
  curric:id "2892"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.025563Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
