    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-be-being ,
    oakcurric:thread-negation ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions .

oakcurric:unit-2933
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "School exchange: verbs with prepositions"@en ;
  curric:slug "school-exchange-verbs-with-prepositions" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits the present tense, introducing sentences with two objects, and
  verbs with direct or indirect objects. Verbs with prepositions an, auf, für and vor are
  introduced."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Building on prior knowledge of present tense of verbs with indirect
  objects, this unit introduces sentences with two objects and verbs with direct or indirect
  objects. Pupils revise indirect object pronouns 'uns' and 'ihnen' and learn 'euch;. Pupils
  practise this in the context of preparing for a school exchange, and in talking about the
  things they do for others. Pupils then learn how to use verbs with prepositions 'an,'auf',
  'für' and 'vor' (reflexive and non-reflexive) to give their reactions and express feelings
  about an exchange.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2933-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2933-2 ;
  curric:id "2933"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.859108Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners .

oakcurric:unit-2899
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Activities: time phrases, word order, prepositions"@en ;
  curric:slug "activities-time-phrases-word-order-prepositions" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces word order 2 for sentences starting with time adverbs. It
  contrasts word order 1 and 2 when describing what others do and when. Pupils then apply
  these rules to question forms. The dative case is introduced to describe location, plus
  sound-symbol correspondences [th] and [st]."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils' prior understanding strong and weak verbs.
  With the introduction of new vocabulary including time adverbials, they develop their
  knowledge in talking about when they do things. They will explore changes in word order when
  using time phrases and how to apply these to both statements and questions. Later in the
  unit, they will learn about the use of different cases (accusative and dative) to express
  movement or location with 'in' and 'auf'. This lays the foundation for later units addressing
  movement versus location.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2899-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2899-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2899-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2899-4 ;
  curric:id "2899"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.961506Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions .

oakcurric:unit-2932
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Positive experiences: word order and prepositions"@en ;
  curric:slug "positive-experiences-word-order-and-prepositions" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits a broad range of known grammar and vocabulary and introduces
  'um...zu' +infinitive. New imperfect modals sollte and durfte are practised, together with
  further consolidation of Time-Manner-Place word order. Prepositions and cases for movement
  and location are consolidated."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit expands pupils' ability to answer the question 'why' as they
  learn 'um...zu + infinitive' to express reasons. Pupils explore this in the context of
  helping others. They reactivate knowledge of past tense, word order (time, manner, place) in
  saying when, how and where they do things when describing journeys past and present. And they
  consolidate knowledge of prepositions and accusative and dative with articles with verbs of
  movement and location. Reflexive verbs are revisited and pupils practise talking about what
  goes where in a familiar context of making changes at home.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2932-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2932-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2932-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2932-4 ;
  curric:id "2932"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.042289Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past .

oakcurric:unit-2894
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Life at home: present tense (singular) weak verbs"@en ;
  curric:slug "life-at-home-present-tense-singular-weak-verbs" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces pupils to verb infinitives and the patterns for weak
  (regular) high frequency verbs in the 1st and 3rd persons singular. Pupils learn how to
  use them in familiar contexts at school and at home. They practise sound-symbol
  correspondences long and short [o] and [i]."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils build on their knowledge of weak verbs and closed and
  open question forms. As the unit progresses, they will consolidate and apply their knowledge
  by building sentences from infinitives in a familiar context.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2894-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2894-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2894-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2894-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2894-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2894-6 ;
  curric:id "2894"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.054705Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-use-reference-resources ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order .

oakcurric:unit-2922
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "My plans: future tense"@en ;
  curric:slug "my-plans-future-tense" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits a range of learning from previous units, principally the future
  tense and tw0 verb structures, and infinitive clauses with 'zu'. Pronouns are revisited as
  well as word order 3 with 'wenn'."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils consolidate their knowledge of the future tense and
  the two-verb rule, with further practice in question formation and word order changes. They
  learn how to add detail to their descriptions, using the conjunction 'wenn', and word order
  3. Pronouns (subject, direct and indirect objects) are revisited as pupils talk about the
  things that are important to them for their future. Authentic adapted texts are used,
  building pupils' confidence from earlier units in their ability to tackle more complex texts
  with a secure knowledge of high frequency vocabulary.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2922-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2922-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2922-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2922-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2922-5 ;
  curric:id "2922"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.134161Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts .

oakcurric:unit-2925
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Past lives: perfect and imperfect tenses"@en ;
  curric:slug "past-lives-perfect-and-imperfect-tenses" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits past tenses. The perfect tense is consolidated as variations on
  past participle formation are practised. The imperfect tense (war, hatte, es gab) is
  revisited, with question formation and word order 3 conjunctions. Pupils learn how to say
  calendar years in German."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit extends pupils' knowledge of the German perfect tense with haben
  and sein to include all persons including 'ihr'. Past participle formation is consolidated as
  pupils recall and practise stem change and other variations. Pupils apply this in the context
  of studying lives of famous German speakers past and present. The imperfect tense is
  revisited, together with word order 3, and 'bevor', 'nachdem' and 'als' (meaning when in the
  past tense). Towards the end of the unit this is practised in the context of past experiences
  in former East and West Germany.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2925-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2925-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2925-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2925-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2925-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2925-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2925-7 ;
  curric:id "2925"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.712290Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past .

oakcurric:unit-2935
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "The environment: verbs of opinion"@en ;
  curric:slug "the-environment-verbs-of-opinion" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit extends pupils' knowledge of verbs and prepositions by introducing wo-
  and da- compounds wo/darauf, wo/dafür, wo/damit, wo/davor and wo/darüber. Conversational
  particles (doch, echt, natürlich) are introduced to facilitate a discussion on
  environmental issues."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils build on knowledge of verbs with prepositions and
  learn how to us 'da-' and 'wo-' with prepositions to refer back to things. With the use of
  known and some new vocabulary pupils apply their knowledge to read, listen and talk about
  concerns for the environment. And using modal verbs, verbs of opinion and two-verb
  structures, pupils develop their questions and answers to present a case during a discussion
  using extended opinions using dass and word order 3.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2935-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2935-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2935-3 ;
  curric:id "2935"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.716065Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-2896
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Opinions about school: 'mögen', 'finden' and object pronouns"@en ;
  curric:slug "opinions-about-school-mogen-finden-and-object-pronouns" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores giving opinions, using 'mögen' and 'finden' with a range of
  adjectives, used here in the context of school. It analyses how to use the correct object
  pronoun for the gender of the noun it refers to, including how to distinguish 'the object
  pronoun 'sie' in singular and plural."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit continues to develop pupils' ability and language range to talk
  about the familiar context of school. It builds on their knowledge of weak verbs, and subject
  pronouns, and as the unit progresses, pupils will apply their knowledge and new vocabulary to
  give opinions accurately with the use of object pronouns.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2896-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2896-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2896-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2896-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2896-5 ;
  curric:id "2896"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.751142Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-negation ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions .

oakcurric:unit-2936
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Places and projects: imperfect modal verbs"@en ;
  curric:slug "places-and-projects-imperfect-modal-verbs" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit consolidates grammar knowledge of word order - time before manner before
  place - and revisits imperfect modals. The present and perfect tense are revisited with
  verbs plus indirect objects."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit revisits previously learnt vocabulary and grammar as pupils talk
  and write about past journeys. Pupils' knowledge of Germany is enriched as the learn of
  journey to the German islands of Helgoland, Röhr and Rügen. Knowledge of present and perfect
  tenses with indirect objects is applied as learn about young German celebrities and pupils
  talk about planning a charity concert.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2936-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2936-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2936-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2936-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2936-5 ;
  curric:id "2936"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.752931Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-negation ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-2923
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Modern lives and tall tales: present tense"@en ;
  curric:slug "modern-lives-and-tall-tales-present-tense" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits previously known vocabulary and the present tense in new
  contexts. . The 2nd person plural 'ihr' (informal) is introduced for weak verbs and the
  contrasts between du and 'Sie' (formal) consolidated."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit reactivates prior knowledge of known vocabulary and the present
  tense. Pupils consolidate their understanding of the two different English translations of
  the German present tense (general activities I do, vs current activities - I am doing).) The
  2nd person plural 'ihr' form of weak verbs, sein and haben is introduced and practised.
  German pop stars provide context, with pupils preparing interview questions. Pupils undertake
  a paired 'fairy tale' narration, in which their knowledge of verbs with indirect objects and
  prior vocabulary learning are revisited in a novel context.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2923-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2923-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2923-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2923-4 ;
  curric:id "2923"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.792952Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-2921
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Erlkönig (Johann Wolfgang von Goethe): read and respond to a poem"@en ;
  curric:slug "erlkonig-johann-wolfgang-von-goethe-read-and-respond-to-a-poem" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils read and respond to a famous German poem, understanding how
  known and some new high frequency vocabulary can make extended literary texts accessible
  and rewarding."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils consolidate existing and learn new high frequency
  vocabulary in the context of a famous German poem. They then apply this vocabulary to
  describe their reaction to the poem, deepen their knowledge of definite and indefinite
  articles, and develop confidence in extended reading.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2921-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2921-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2921-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2921-4 ;
  curric:id "2921"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.880688Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-listen-and-respond-to-longer-passages ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts .

oakcurric:unit-2911
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "A party: separable verbs"@en ;
  curric:slug "a-party-separable-verbs" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces separable verbs, teaching pupils how to manipulate these in
  sentences in short form and infinitive, with two verb structures and with 'nicht'. Word
  order 1 and 3 are revisited with the conjunctions 'denn and 'während'. Pupils learn to
  distinguish placement and position verbs."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces separable verbs in the previously taught present
  tense in the context of a party. Pupils learn the structure of separable verbs in standard
  sentences, and as an infinitive in two-verb structures. Previous knowledge of word order in
  negation is revisited with separable verbs. Cultural context features with the international
  hot air balloon festival in Switzerland. Pupils also revisit their knowledge of movement vs
  location by revisiting accusative and dative with the richer vocabulary of high frequency
  German variations of the verb ' to put'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2911-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2911-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2911-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2911-4 ;
  curric:id "2911"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.882298Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order .

